ASABA – Gunmen alleged to be herdsmen Wednesday kidnapped Urhobo gospel singer, Evangelist Jerry Ekpekurho, along the Osubi/Eku Road in Okpe Local Government Area of Delta State. Daily Independent gathered that the Urhobo music legend was waylaid by gunmen who forcefully whisked him to an un­known destination. It was learnt that the vehicle of the victim was left behind by the kidnappers along the road which prompted relations to suspect it was a case of abduction. EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! It was further gathered that the abductors were said to have contacted the family of the musi­cian demanding for N50 million to free him. Several Urhobo musicians con­firmed the abduction of their col­league on Wednesday. Tears Of Joy As Missing 15-Year- Old Blessing Reunites With Family Agency Confiscates Alcoholic Drinks Worth N25m Police sources in Osubi and Orerokpe confirmed the incident, saying a rescue team has been launched to secure the release of the musician. When contacted, Delta Po­lice Public Relations Officer (PPRO), DSP Onome Onovwak­poyeya, confirmed the incident but could not give details of the incident. SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION